  FRENCH VERSION
  --------------
  If you speak  - or understand -  only French langage, there is no French
  version yet available.


  PURPOSE
  -------
  This document explains how to set up pwCorePlugin within a whole symfony
  application, and thus it's mostly dedicated to developers.


  REQUIREMENTS
  ------------
  Plugins: 
    sfFormExtraPlugin,
    sfJqueryReloadedPlugin,
    sfDoctrineGuardPlugin (version 5.0.0),
    csDoctrineActAsGeolocatablePlugin (version 2.0.1)
    sfEasyGMapPlugin (version 3.1.0)
  We suppose these plugins have been properly installed.


  1) Folders
  ----------

  Link the root plugin folder to /path/to/sf_project/plugins/pwCorePlugin


  2) Declare the plugin
  ---------------------

  Jump to your ProjectConfiguration.class.php and add 'pwCorePlugin' to the
  list of enabled plugins into enablePlugins().


  3) Build form and model classes
  -------------------------------

  > php symfony doctrine:build-forms
  > php symfony doctrine:build-models


  4) Publish assets
  -----------------

  > php symfony plugin:publish-assets


  5) Update myUser class
  ----------------------

  This class extends the sfBasicSecurityUser class, but now it should
  extend pwUser.


  6) Set the homepage
  -------------------

  The homepage of your application needs to be set. Open the file
  /apps/your_app/config/routing.yml and update the 'homepage' route to
  login module and login action. Your line should look like the following :

    + - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - +
    |                                                 |
    | homepage:                                       |
    |   url:   /                                      |
    |   param: { module: login, action: login }       |
    |                                                 |
    + - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - +


  7) Merge CSS and JS files
  -------------------------

  Use minifiers tools (YUI compressor, for example) to merge and minify CSS and
  JS files. Then update view.yml file to include new generated files.
